---
import Layout from "../../../layouts/LayoutDue.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Due's privacy policy: what data the app stores, where it lives, and what — if anything — leaves your device."
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
      <h1>Privacy policy</h1>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content">
    <div class="wrap legal-content">
      <span class="legal-updated">Last updated: {new Date().toLocaleDateString("en-US", { year: "numeric", month: "long", day: "numeric" })}</span>

      <h2>The short version</h2>
      <p>
        Due doesn't have a server, an account system, or an analytics provider. The bills you add their names, amounts, due dates, and payment status, are stored only in your device's local
        storage. Nobody but you, on your device, has access to that information. That's the whole
        policy; everything below just explains it in more detail.
      </p>

      <h2>What Due stores, and where</h2>
      <p>
        When you add a bill, Due saves it using Apple's on-device data storage (SwiftData), on your
        phone. This data is never transmitted to us, to a server, or to any third party. If you
        delete the app, that data is deleted with it. Due has no way to retrieve it, because Due
        never had a copy in the first place.
      </p>

      <h2>Notifications</h2>
      <p>
        Reminders are scheduled locally on your device using Apple's notification system. Due does
        not use a push notification service, which means no bill data is ever sent off your phone to
        trigger a reminder.
      </p>

      <h2>Exporting your data</h2>
      <p>
        Due lets you export your bills to a file for backup purposes. That file is created and
        stored using the standard iOS share sheet, entirely under your control. Due does not upload
        it anywhere, and has no visibility into where you choose to save or send it.
      </p>

      <h2>In-app tips</h2>
      <p>
        Due offers optional, one-time tips to support development. These purchases are processed
        entirely by Apple through StoreKit. Due does not receive or store your payment information. Apple handles the transaction, and any billing details are covered by Apple's own privacy
        policy, not this one.
      </p>

      <h2>Children's privacy</h2>
      <p>
        Due does not knowingly collect any information from anyone, including children, because Due
        does not collect information from anyone at all, data stays on-device regardless of who's
        using it.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        If this policy ever changes, for example, if a future version of Due adds an optional
        feature that involves a network connection, this page will be updated, and the "last
        updated" date above will reflect it.
      </p>

      <!-- <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about this policy can be sent to <a href="mailto:support@example.com">support@example.com</a>.
      </p> -->
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .page-hero {
    background: var(--cream);
    padding: 72px 0 48px;
  }

  .eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 12px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    color: var(--forest);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .page-hero h1 {
    font-size: clamp(30px, 4vw, 42px);
  }

  .content {
    padding: 48px 0 96px;
  }

  .legal-content {
    max-width: 680px;
  }
</style>